   <concept id="FAR_39_204"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">39.204</ph> Exceptions.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <p id="d2454e8" class="- topic/p ">The requirements in <xref href="39.203.dita#FAR_39_203"
                  base="i1077016"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">39.203</xref> do not apply to EIT that-</p>
         <ol id="d2427e22" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2449e15" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            Is purchased in accordance with <xref href="Subpart_13.2.dita#FAR_Subpart_13_2"
                        base="i1111868"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpartÂ  13.2</xref> (micro-purchases) prior to April 1,2005. However, for micro-purchases, contracting officers and other individuals designated in accordance with <xref href="1.603-3.dita#FAR_1_603_3"
                        base="i1126501"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">1.603-3</xref> are strongly encouraged to comply with the applicable accessibility standards to the maximum extent practicable;</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2449e26" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
						            Is for a national security system;</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2449e31" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
						            Is acquired by a contractor incidental to a contract;</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2449e36" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
						            Is located in spaces frequented only by service personnel for maintenance, repair or occasional monitoring of equipment; or</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2449e41" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
						            Would impose an undue burden on the agency.</p>
               <ol id="d2427e74" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2449e47" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Basis</i>. In determining whether compliance with all or part of the applicable accessibility standards in <ph outputclass="CFR" class="- topic/ph ">36 CFR Part 1194</ph> would be an undue burden, an agency must consider-</p>
                     <ol id="d2427e87" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d2449e58" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
										                    The difficulty or expense of compliance; and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d2449e63" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
										                    Agency resources available to its program or component for which the supply or service is being acquired.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2449e68" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
								                Documentation.</p>
                     <ol id="d2427e117" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d2449e74" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
										                    The requiring official must document in writing the basis for an undue burden decision and provide the documentation to the contracting officer for inclusion in the contract file.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d2449e79" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
										                    When acquiring commercial items, an undue burden determination is not required to address individual standards that cannot be met with supplies or service available in the commercial marketplace in time to meet the agency delivery requirements (see <xref href="39.203.dita#FAR_39_203"
                                    base="i1077016"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">39.203</xref>(c)(2) regarding documentation of nonavailability).</p>
                           <p id="d2449e86" class="- topic/p "/>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
